Yes, I am taking some cues from Chimera Squad to flesh out bits of some character. The majority of it is nothing but headcanon. For example, the passage from the latest chapter where Vee says how Vipers would help each other shade in a pseudo-communal nature -- I pulled that out of thin air from the shedding rock you can find in an apartment in chimera Squad, with the many skins lying around it.

City 31 is also described in the lore as fairly accepting even so early after the war. Text from Chimera Squad states that there were almost no reprisal attacks in the city after ADVENT fell and that business carried on mostly as usual. However, animosity still dominates much of the rest of the world; even five years later in Chimera's setting, City 31 is a model city. That means everywhere else is still most likely shit and people are looking towards 31 to see if living with aliens is even possible.

At my best I used to do 14k over a two day weekend.
Now I'm lucky to do 1k a day, or 20k a month.

If you're unafraid to go off on a tangent because of a great idea that's a different story - all to keep from burning out - it's a net positive.

The only negative is saying you suck until that's all you believe.
